## 1. Variables in Julia

Julia uses normal assignment with `=`.

### Basic example

```julia
name = "Anthony"
age = 32
wants_web_apps = true

println(name)
println(age)
println(wants_web_apps)
```

### One-line output

```julia
name = "Anthony"
age = 32
wants_web_apps = true

println(name, " ", age, " ", wants_web_apps)
```

### Compare with earlier languages

Python:

```python
name = "Anthony"
```

R:

```r
name <- "Anthony"
```

Julia:

```julia
name = "Anthony"
```

### Real-world example: web app cart total

```julia
product_name = "basketball"
item_price = 3.23
quantity = 25
total_cost = item_price * quantity

println(product_name, " ", total_cost)
```

### Real-world example: scientific conversion

```julia
celsius = 22.5
fahrenheit = (celsius * 9 / 5) + 32

println(fahrenheit)
```

