## 2. Conditionals in Julia

Julia uses `if`, `elseif`, and `else`, ending the whole block with `end`.

```julia
age = 17

if age >= 18
    println("Adult")
else
    println("Minor")
end
```

### Web app example: role access

```julia
role = "editor"

if role == "admin"
    println("Full access")
elseif role == "editor"
    println("Can edit content")
elseif role == "viewer"
    println("Read-only access")
else
    println("Unknown role")
end
```

### Compare with Python

Python:

```python
if age >= 18:
    print("Adult")
else:
    print("Minor")
```

Julia:

```julia
if age >= 18
    println("Adult")
else
    println("Minor")
end
```

Main difference:

* Python uses `:`
* Julia uses `end`

