## 4. Functions in Julia

Functions are defined with `function ... end`, though there is also a shorter one-line style.

### Basic function

```julia
function say_hello()
    println("Hello!")
end

say_hello()
```

### Function with parameter

```julia
function greet_person(name)
    println("Hello, ", name, "!")
end

greet_person("Anthony")
```

### Function with return value

```julia
function multiply_numbers(num1, num2)
    return num1 * num2
end

result = multiply_numbers(3, 6)
println(result)
```

### Real-world example: tax calculation

```julia
function add_tax(price, tax_rate)
    return price + (price * tax_rate)
end

final_price = add_tax(100, 0.06)
println(final_price)
```

### Short form

```julia
add_tax(price, tax_rate) = price + (price * tax_rate)
```

